net.objectof

Interface Context<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of object emitted by the Context.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Named
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Package, Runtime<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IAggregateInterface, IContext, IFaceted, IInterface, IKind, ILoadableContext, ILoadableInterface, IPackage, IPeer, IRepo, IRepoType, IRip, IRipType, IRuntime, IRuntimes, ISource, ISourcePackage, ISpringContext, ISqlDb, ISQLite, ISqlRepo, ITemplateContext, IUtilContext

    public interface Context<T>
extends Named
    A Context can emit objects associated to a name. Generally the names are component names as defined in Named. A Context that:
    • contains a set of named persistent or singleton objects is known as a scope
    • creates new objects based on a name is known as a factory.
    A Context can be both a scope and factory.
    Author:
    jdh

    • Method Detail

      • forName

        T forName(java.lang.String aComponentName)
        Parameters:
        aComponentName - A name identifying the singleton or a type of instance to return.
        Returns:
        An object for aComponentName or null. This interface doesn't specify any constraints on the object that is returned for each invocation: i.e. there is no requirement that the same object or null or a different object will be returned for repeated calls to this even when the same name is specified.
        Throws:
        InvalidNameException - When aComponentName is not known by this Context.
        java.lang.ClassCastException - When this Context reifies the generic type and the name references an object whose type is not assignable to the reified type.
